 LINUS CHIBUIKE PRESIDENT Muhammadu Buhari has congratulated former Minister of Mines and Steel Development, Chief Sarafa Tunji Ishola, on his 60th birthday. The President, in a statement on Friday, signed by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, said he was felicitating with the Ambassador-Designate for his many achievements over the years, particularly his contribution to the development of Ogun State, where he held many positions. Adesina said, “President Muhammadu Buhari sends warm greetings to former Minister of Mines and Steel, Alhaji Sarafadeen Tunji Isola, on his 60th birthday, joining family, friends and political associates to rejoice with the Ambassador-Designate on the milestone. “The President felicitates with the former minister for his many achievements over the years, particularly his contribution to the development of Ogun State, where he held key political positions, before serving at the national level, with a high sense of patriotism. “As Isola marks 60 years, the President believes his wealth of experience will be most useful to the country at this time, considering his background in community development and grassroots mobilisation. “President Buhari prays that the Almighty God will continue to endue the former Minister with longer life and good health.”  